  <h1>Privacy Policy – Number Game</h1>
  <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> November 2025</p>
  <p><strong>Developer:</strong> R. Rajeshkannan</p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We collect anonymous identifiers, device info, and game progress data via Firebase.</p>

  <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
  <p>Data is used to save progress, maintain leaderboards, and improve gameplay.</p>

  <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>We use Firebase Authentication, Firestore, Storage, and Analytics. See <a href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy">Firebase Privacy</a>.</p>

  <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
  <p>All communication uses secure HTTPS. We never sell your data.</p>

  <h2>5. Children’s Privacy</h2>
  <p>This game does not collect personal information from children knowingly.</p>

  <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>Contact <a href="mailto:rajeshkannan.dev@gmail.com">rajeshkannan.dev@gmail.com</a> to delete or review your data.</p>

  <h2>7. Updates</h2>
  <p>Policy updates will appear here as we improve our game and services.</p>
